<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFEE6A51FD2E97F21D6FB9BF" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFEE6A51FD2E97F21D6FB9BF" blockId="21.[721,1313,313,731]" pageId="21" pageNumber="779">
Taxonomic affinities of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEE6A51FBDB97F21AAABAFA" box="[1063,1194,427,456]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sturdeei">P. sturdeei</taxonomicName>
are currently uncertain because it is known only from a single specimen with uncertainty as to where the type specimen is from and thus where the species might still occur. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
