<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFEE6A51FF9293521AADBE90" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFEE6A51FF9293521AADBE90" blockId="21.[108,1314,738,1481]" pageId="21" pageNumber="779">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFEE6A51FF9293521FCBBE1E" bold="true" box="[110,459,1291,1324]" pageId="21" pageNumber="779">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Sturdee’s Pipistrelle is currently known only from a single specimen collected at the end of the 19 century. It was listed as Extinct in 1996 and 2004 butlisted as Data Deficient in 2006 and 2008 because there is uncertainty regarding where the species might still occur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
